<subSubSection id="C344654D632B501B9EF4FB50CDEFF919" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE136C6632B501B9EF4FB50CDEFF919" blockId="2.[151,1437,1148,1859]" pageId="2" pageNumber="465">
<emphasis id="B92AEAD4632B501B9EF4FB50CE6FFB3C" bold="true" box="[199,322,1220,1246]" pageId="2" pageNumber="465">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF4B37632B501B9F79FB50CEDFFB3D" author="Schmid" box="[330,498,1220,1247]" firstAuthor="Schmid" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" pagination="1 - 173" refId="ref8245" refString="Schmid, F. (1958) Trichopteres de Ceylan. Archiv fur Hydrobiologie, 54 (1 - 2), 1 - 173." type="journal article" year="1958">Schmid (1958)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D45632B501B9C4FFB51CC23FB3C" box="[636,782,1220,1246]" class="Insecta" family="Odontoceridae" genus="Marilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ceylanica">
<emphasis id="B92AEAD4632B501B9C4FFB51CC23FB3C" box="[636,782,1220,1246]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="465">M. ceylanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D45632B501B9DC9FB51CA2BFB3D" authority="(Hagen 1858)" baseAuthorityName="Hagen" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[1018,1286,1220,1247]" class="Insecta" family="Odontoceridae" genus="Marilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mixta">
<emphasis id="B92AEAD4632B501B9DC9FB51CB72FB3C" box="[1018,1119,1221,1246]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="465">M. mixta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF4B37632B501B9A5CFB51CBD0FB3D" author="Hagen" box="[1135,1277,1220,1247]" firstAuthor="Hagen" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" pagination="484 - 487" refId="ref5938" refString="Hagen, H. A. (1858) Synopsis der Neuropteren Ceylons. Part 1. Verhandlungen der Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wein, 8, 484 - 487." type="journal article" year="1858">Hagen 1858</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF4B37632B501B9B0CFB50CFCFFAE1" author="Malicky" firstAuthor="Malicky" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref6303" refString="Malicky, H. (1989) Odontoceridae aus Thailand (Trichoptera). Opuscula Zoologica Fluminensia, 36, 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="1989">Malicky (1989)</bibRefCitation>
deemed 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D45632B501B9F78FB7DCEF0FAE0" box="[331,477,1256,1282]" class="Insecta" family="Odontoceridae" genus="Marilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ceylanica">
<emphasis id="B92AEAD4632B501B9F78FB7DCEF0FAE0" box="[331,477,1256,1282]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="465">M. ceylanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be a valid species. The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D45632B501B9DEEFB7DCB42FAE0" box="[989,1135,1256,1282]" class="Insecta" family="Odontoceridae" genus="Marilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ceylanica">
<emphasis id="B92AEAD4632B501B9DEEFB7DCB42FAE0" box="[989,1135,1256,1282]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="465">M. ceylanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D45632B501B9B4DFB7DCE8CFAC5" authority="Ulmer 1951" authorityName="Ulmer" authorityYear="1951" class="Insecta" family="Odontoceridae" genus="Marilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sumatrana">
<emphasis id="B92AEAD4632B501B9B4DFB7DCE22FAC4" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="465">M. sumatrana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF4B37632B501B9F24FA98CE8CFAC5" author="Ulmer" box="[279,417,1292,1319]" firstAuthor="Ulmer" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" pagination="1 - 528" refId="ref8598" refString="Ulmer, G. (1951) Kocherfliegen (Trichopteren) von den Sunda-Inseln. Teil I. Archiv fur Hydrobiologie, Supplement 19, 1 - 528." type="journal article" year="1951">Ulmer 1951</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. However, in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D45632B501B9C0CFA99CDFDFAC4" box="[575,720,1292,1318]" class="Insecta" family="Odontoceridae" genus="Marilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ceylanica">
<emphasis id="B92AEAD4632B501B9C0CFA99CDFDFAC4" box="[575,720,1292,1318]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="465">M. ceylanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, segment IX is without any angular horizontal plates above the bases of the preanal appendages (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF4B37632B501B9C20FAA4CD98FAA9" author="Malicky" box="[531,693,1328,1355]" firstAuthor="Malicky" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref6303" refString="Malicky, H. (1989) Odontoceridae aus Thailand (Trichoptera). Opuscula Zoologica Fluminensia, 36, 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="1989">Malicky 1989</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF4B37632B501B9CF1FAA5CC59FAA9" author="Martynov" box="[706,884,1328,1355]" firstAuthor="Martynov" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" pagination="239 - 306" refId="ref7186" refString="Martynov, A. V. (1936) On a collection of Trichoptera from the Indian Museum Part II- Integripalpia. Records of Indian Museum, 38, 239 - 306" type="journal article" year="1936">Martynov 1936</bibRefCitation>
); but in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D45632B501B9DE0FAA5CB5FFAA8" authorityName="Ulmer" authorityYear="1951" box="[979,1138,1329,1354]" class="Insecta" family="Odontoceridae" genus="Marilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sumatrana">
<emphasis id="B92AEAD4632B501B9DE0FAA5CB5FFAA8" box="[979,1138,1329,1354]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="465">M. sumatrana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
segment IX bears angular horizontal plates in that position (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF4B37632B501B9C2AFAC0CD90FA8D" author="Malicky" box="[537,701,1364,1391]" firstAuthor="Malicky" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref6303" refString="Malicky, H. (1989) Odontoceridae aus Thailand (Trichoptera). Opuscula Zoologica Fluminensia, 36, 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="1989">Malicky 1989</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF4B37632B501B9CF9FAC1CC2AFA8D" author="Malicky, H." box="[714,775,1365,1391]" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" pagination="87 - 95" refId="ref6632" refString="Malicky, H. (2010) Kocherfliegen (Trichoptera) von der Noona Dan Expedition 1961 - 1962 zu den Philippinen, dem Bismark-Archipel und den Salomon-Inseln. Zeitschrift der Arbeitsgemeinschaft Osterreichischer Entomologen, 62, 87 - 95." type="journal article" year="2010">2010</bibRefCitation>
). [
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF4B37632B501B9D12FAC0CC92FA8D" author="Ulmer" box="[801,959,1364,1391]" firstAuthor="Ulmer" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" pagination="1 - 528" refId="ref8598" refString="Ulmer, G. (1951) Kocherfliegen (Trichopteren) von den Sunda-Inseln. Teil I. Archiv fur Hydrobiologie, Supplement 19, 1 - 528." type="journal article" year="1951">Ulmer (1951)</bibRefCitation>
described and illustrated tergum X of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D45632B501B9B4DFAC1CE22FA70" authorityName="Ulmer" authorityYear="1951" class="Insecta" family="Odontoceridae" genus="Marilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sumatrana">
<emphasis id="B92AEAD4632B501B9B4DFAC1CE22FA70" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="465">M. sumatrana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without any apical notch in dorsal view, but 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF4B37632B501B9D22FAECCCECFA71" author="Malicky" box="[785,961,1400,1427]" firstAuthor="Malicky" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref6303" refString="Malicky, H. (1989) Odontoceridae aus Thailand (Trichoptera). Opuscula Zoologica Fluminensia, 36, 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="1989">Malicky (1989)</bibRefCitation>
considered that supposed difference from 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D45632B501B9EA4FA09CE04FA54" box="[151,297,1436,1462]" class="Insecta" family="Odontoceridae" genus="Marilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ceylanica">
<emphasis id="B92AEAD4632B501B9EA4FA09CE04FA54" box="[151,297,1436,1462]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="465">M. ceylanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be an artifact.] Furthermore, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF4B37632B501B9CA8FA08CC66FA55" author="Malicky" box="[667,843,1436,1463]" firstAuthor="Malicky" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref6303" refString="Malicky, H. (1989) Odontoceridae aus Thailand (Trichoptera). Opuscula Zoologica Fluminensia, 36, 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="1989">Malicky (1989)</bibRefCitation>
compared specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D45632B501B9A5AFA09CA25FA54" authorityName="Ulmer" authorityYear="1951" box="[1129,1288,1437,1462]" class="Insecta" family="Odontoceridae" genus="Marilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sumatrana">
<emphasis id="B92AEAD4632B501B9A5AFA09CA25FA54" box="[1129,1288,1437,1462]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="465">M. sumatrana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(populations from Sumatra and 
<collectingCountry id="F3497656632B501B9F5FFA54CEFCFA39" box="[364,465,1472,1499]" name="Thailand" pageId="2" pageNumber="465">Thailand</collectingCountry>
) with specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D45632B501B9C8BFA55CC67FA38" box="[696,842,1472,1498]" class="Insecta" family="Odontoceridae" genus="Marilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ceylanica">
<emphasis id="B92AEAD4632B501B9C8BFA55CC67FA38" box="[696,842,1472,1498]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="465">M. ceylanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and noted that, in addition to the difference in male genitalia, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D45632B501B9F34FA71CEB4FA1C" box="[263,409,1508,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Odontoceridae" genus="Marilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ceylanica">
<emphasis id="B92AEAD4632B501B9F34FA71CEB4FA1C" box="[263,409,1508,1534]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="465">M. ceylanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D45632B501B9D2FFA71CC96FA1C" authorityName="Ulmer" authorityYear="1951" box="[796,955,1509,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Odontoceridae" genus="Marilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sumatrana">
<emphasis id="B92AEAD4632B501B9D2FFA71CC96FA1C" box="[796,955,1509,1534]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="465">M. sumatrana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of additional characters: “the great geographical distance between them, the difference in size (
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D45632B501B9D5DF99DCCD3F9C0" box="[878,1022,1544,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Odontoceridae" genus="Marilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ceylanica">
<emphasis id="B92AEAD4632B501B9D5DF99DCCD3F9C0" box="[878,1022,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="465">M. ceylanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only half the size), and in the male forewing of the Thai species [
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D45632B501B9FDBF9B9CDA8F9A4" authorityName="Ulmer" authorityYear="1951" box="[488,645,1581,1606]" class="Insecta" family="Odontoceridae" genus="Marilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sumatrana">
<emphasis id="B92AEAD4632B501B9FDBF9B9CDA8F9A4" box="[488,645,1581,1606]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="465">M. sumatrana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
] the veins R4, R5 and M1+2 (sensu Ulmer) arise practically from one point, in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D45632B501B9EC8F9C5CEA6F988" box="[251,395,1616,1642]" class="Insecta" family="Odontoceridae" genus="Marilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ceylanica">
<emphasis id="B92AEAD4632B501B9EC8F9C5CEA6F988" box="[251,395,1616,1642]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="465">M. ceylanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the last two form a fork” [translated from German]. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF4B37632B501B9DE4F9C4CBABF989" author="Malicky" box="[983,1158,1616,1643]" firstAuthor="Malicky" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" pagination="41 - 54" refId="ref6674" refString="Malicky, H. (2013) Synonyms and possible synonyms of Asiatic Trichoptera / Synonyme und mogliche Synonyme von asiatischen Kocherfliegen. Braueria, 40, 41 - 54." type="journal article" year="2013">Malicky (2013)</bibRefCitation>
more recently expressed his frustration for diagnosis of most species in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D45632B501B9C95F9E0CDD1F96C" authorityName="Mueller" authorityYear="1880" box="[678,764,1652,1678]" class="Insecta" family="Odontoceridae" genus="Marilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92AEAD4632B501B9C95F9E0CDD1F96C" box="[678,764,1652,1678]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="465">Marilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as follows: “So we have to realize that our current methods of species identification in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D45632B501B9C06F90CCDA6F950" authorityName="Mueller" authorityYear="1880" box="[565,651,1688,1714]" class="Insecta" family="Odontoceridae" genus="Marilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92AEAD4632B501B9C06F90CCDA6F950" box="[565,651,1688,1714]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="465">Marilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are insufficient and that any attempt at identification is a pure game of chance” [translated from German]. Future revisionary work combining morphological and molecular studies could provide better insight to the species of this genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C344654D632B501B9EF4F890CED1F8A0" pageId="2" pageNumber="465" type="distribution">
